apversionFW.name: apversionFW
apversionFW.description: Main firmware version. Format: <code version>H<hardware version>D<date>.

apsystemBaseId.name: apsystemBaseId
apsystemBaseId.description: Cluster that the AP belongs to. All APs and SUs in the same cluster shall have the same Base ID.

apsystemAPId.name: apsystemAPId
apsystemAPId.description: AP ID. Each AP in a cluster shall have unique AP ID.

apsystemDefOpMode.name: apsystemDefOpMode
apsystemDefOpMode.description: The operation mode (ap or off) the radio is on after reboot/power cycle.

apsystemActivateOpmode.name: apsystemActivateOpmode
apsystemActivateOpmode.description: Engage AP unit to ap operation mode.

apsystemReadCommStr.name: apsystemReadCommStr
apsystemReadCommStr.description: SNMP agent read community string. It is used for authentication purpose.

apsystemWriteCommStr.name: apsystemWriteCommStr
apsystemWriteCommStr.description: SNMP agent write community string. It is used for authentication purpose.

apswitchesBlockBroadcastMulticast.name: apswitchesBlockBroadcastMulticast
apswitchesBlockBroadcastMulticast.description: This switch enables or disables the blocking of Ethernet control packet except ICMP and ARP to reduce the amount of uneccessary overhead introduced to the wireless link.

apswitchesSUtoSU.name: apswitchesSUtoSU
apswitchesSUtoSU.description: This switch enables or disables the peer-to-peer feature among SUs through the AP. Before this switch is turned on, all SUs that want to communicate with each other have to be assigned to the same group.

apswitchesTFTPD.name: apswitchesTFTPD
apswitchesTFTPD.description: This switch enables or disables the TFTP operation. When it is turned on, then the AP will be ready for code download.

apswitchesHTTPD.name: apswitchesHTTPD
apswitchesHTTPD.description: When it is turned on, then the AP is accessible for configuring via web browser (e.g. IE or Nescape).

apsystemMIRThreshold.name: apsystemMIRThreshold
apsystemMIRThreshold.description: Maximum Information Rate (in Kbps), the AP allows the network to utilize before enforcing CIR on each subscriber.

aptrafficEthRxAvgThroughputLog.name: aptrafficEthRxAvgThroughputLog
aptrafficEthRxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) received on Ethernet port over the last 60 seconds.

aptrafficEthTxAvgThroughputLog.name: aptrafficEthTxAvgThroughputLog
aptrafficEthTxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) transmitted on Ethernet port over the last 60 seconds.

aptrafficRfRxAvgThroughputLog.name: aptrafficRfRxAvgThroughputLog
aptrafficRfRxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) received on RF port over the last 60 seconds.

aptrafficRfTxAvgThroughputLog.name: aptrafficRfTxAvgThroughputLog
aptrafficRfTxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) transmitted on RF port over the last 60 seconds.

aptrafficEthInOctets.name: aptrafficEthInOctets
aptrafficEthInOctets.description: Number of payload octets received on Ethernet port.

aptrafficEthOutOctets.name: aptrafficEthOutOctets
aptrafficEthOutOctets.description: Number of payload octets transmitted on Ethernet port.

aptrafficRfInOctets.name: aptrafficRfInOctets
aptrafficRfInOctets.description: Number of octets of SUs payload received from RF port.

aptrafficRfOutOctets.name: aptrafficRfOutOctets
aptrafficRfOutOctets.description: Number of octets of SUs payload transmitted to RF port.

apsystemUpdateFlashAndActivate.name: apsystemUpdateFlashAndActivate
apsystemUpdateFlashAndActivate.description: Save system setting values to Flash and activate the settings.

apipconfigIpAddress.name: apipconfigIpAddress
apipconfigIpAddress.description: New IP address. It will be saved to non-volatile memory and activated in 5 secs.

apipconfigSubnet.name: apipconfigSubnet
apipconfigSubnet.description: New Subnet mask. It will be saved to non-volatile memory and activated in 5 secs.

apipconfigDefaultGateway.name: apipconfigDefaultGateway
apipconfigDefaultGateway.description: New Default gateway. It will be saved to non-volatile memory and activated in 5 secs.

aprfActiveChannel.name: aprfActiveChannel
aprfActiveChannel.description: It specifies the current channel number the radio operates on.

aprfActivePolarization.name: aprfActivePolarization
aprfActivePolarization.description: It specifies the current polarization the radio operates on.

aprftableChannel1.name: aprftableChannel1
aprftableChannel1.description: RF channel 1 frequency (in MHz). It allows you to create your own channel instead of the manufacturing defaults in the AP. Keep in mind that channel width is 20MHz, and the frequency specified here is the center frequency. Frequency (5260MHz - 5340MHz) is only applicable to M5830S radio.

apismTxPowerMax.name: apismTxPowerMax
apismTxPowerMax.description: The maximum ISM Tx power value can be set (in dBm).

apismTxPowerMin.name: apismTxPowerMin
apismTxPowerMin.description: The minimum ISM Tx power value can be set (in dBm).

apismTxPower.name: apismTxPower
apismTxPower.description: ISM RF tx power (in dBm). It specifies the power output of the radio, excluding the antenna gain. Check parameters apismTxPowerMax and apismTxPowerMin for power setting range.

apismServiceRadius.name: apismServiceRadius
apismServiceRadius.description: ISM RF service radius (in mile). It specifies the distance of the furthest SU the AP will serve. Based on this information, the AP will determine the maximum wait time for a SU to response to a poll before it starts to poll the next one.

apismRxThreshold.name: apismRxThreshold
apismRxThreshold.description: ISM RF rx threshold (in dBm). It specifies the receiver sensitivity of the AP. By default, the radio's sensitivity is -82dBm. The higher the threshold is, the less sensitive the radio will be. In M5800S, the value -90 represents the rfrxthreshold is disabled.

apismTargetRSSI.name: apismTargetRSSI
apismTargetRSSI.description: ISM RF target RSSI (in dBm). It specifies the target RSSI from all SUs to the AP. Based on this parameter, the AP can power level each SU so that it receives same level of signal strength from all SUs, regardless far or near. Note that when you set the Target RSSI from SU, you need to consider AP's RF Rx Threshold value. The Target RSSI from SU must be 5dB higher than the RF Rx Threshold. When the RF Rx Threshold is disabled, the setting of the Target RSSI from SU shall be no less than -75dBm.

apuniiTxPowerMax.name: apuniiTxPowerMax
apuniiTxPowerMax.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S radio. The maximum UNII Tx power value can be set (in dBm).

apuniiTxPowerMin.name: apuniiTxPowerMin
apuniiTxPowerMin.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S radio. The minimum UNII Tx power value can be set (in dBm).

apuniiTxPower.name: apuniiTxPower
apuniiTxPower.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S radio. UNII RF tx power (in dBm). It specifies the power output of the radio, excluding the antenna gain. Check parameters apuniiTxPowerMax and apuniiTxPowerMin for power setting range.

apuniiServiceRadius.name: apuniiServiceRadius
apuniiServiceRadius.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S radio. UNII RF service radius (in mile). It specifies the distance of the furthest SU the AP will serve. Based on this information, the AP will determine the maximum wait time for a SU to response to a poll before it starts to poll the next one.

apuniiRxThreshold.name: apuniiRxThreshold
apuniiRxThreshold.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S radio. UNII RF rx threshold (in dBm). It specifies the receiver sensitivity of the AP.

apuniiTargetRSSI.name: apuniiTargetRSSI
apuniiTargetRSSI.description: This object is only applicable to M5830S radio. UNII RF target RSSI (in dBm). It specifies the target RSSI from all SUs to the AP. Based on this parameter, the AP can power level each SU so that it receives same level of signal strength from all SUs, regardless far or near. Note that when you set the Target RSSI from SU, you need to consider AP's RF Rx Threshold value. The Target RSSI from SU must be 5dB higher than the RF Rx Threshold.

suSUCount.name: suSUCount
suSUCount.description: Number of subscriber units in the subscriber database.

suPowerLvlAll.name: suPowerLvlAll
suPowerLvlAll.description: It is a feature that is typically found in more elaborate mobile systems such as cellular CDMA networks. Using this feature, all SUs have their RF power output adjusted until the signal strength for each SU as received in the AP is roughly the same.

suStatisticsSamplePeriod.name: suStatisticsSamplePeriod
suStatisticsSamplePeriod.description: A period (in minute) AP requests update on SU Info Table from all associated SUs.

suRebootAll.name: suRebootAll
suRebootAll.description: AP broadcasts reboot command to all subscriber units.

sudbDeleteOrAddID.name: sudbDeleteOrAddID
sudbDeleteOrAddID.description: Subscriber unit ID (1..8190). Each subscriber in a sector shall have a unique ID.

sudbAddMAC.name: sudbAddMAC
sudbAddMAC.description: It is the MAC address of the subscriber unit, which can be found on the back of the SU.

sudbAddPolling.name: sudbAddPolling
sudbAddPolling.description: It is service level value, regular or priority, of a SU. The AP will poll priority user more often, thus better network latency as the result. As the network latency varies based on the number of subscriber units the AP serves, priority user is guaranteed that the latency is NOT greater than 100ms regardless of the size of the network.

sudbAddSUtoSU.name: sudbAddSUtoSU
sudbAddSUtoSU.description: It is peer-to-peer group this SU belongs to. With the SU to SU switch is turned on, SUs in the same peer-to-peer group can communicate to each other via the AP. There are totally 15 groups available. Note that the SU shall be set to priority user for this feature to improve latency.

sudbAddCIR.name: sudbAddCIR
sudbAddCIR.description: It is the Committed Information Rate (in Kbps) the AP allocates to SU.

sudbAddMIR.name: sudbAddMIR
sudbAddMIR.description: It is the Maximum Information Rate (in Kbps) the AP allocates to SU.

sudbAdd.name: sudbAdd
sudbAdd.description: Add a subscriber (specified in object sudbDeleteOrAddID) to the subscriber database.

sudbDelete.name: sudbDelete
sudbDelete.description: Delete a subscriber (specified in object sudbDeleteOrAddID) from the subscriber database.

suInfoTable.name: suInfoTable
suInfoTable.description: A table that contains subscriber unit entities.

suInfoEntry.name: suInfoEntry
suInfoEntry.description: Information about a specific subscriber unit retrieved by its ID number.

suID.name: suID
suID.description: Subscriber unit ID. Each subscriber in a sector shall have a unique ID.

suMAC.name: suMAC
suMAC.description: Subscriber unit MAC Address. Format: 00 01 DE xx xx xx.

suPolling.name: suPolling
suPolling.description: It is service level value, regular or priority, of a SU. The AP will poll priority user more often, thus better network latency as the result. As the network latency varies based on the number of subscriber units the AP serves, priority user is guaranteed that the latency is NOT greater than 100ms regardless of the size of the network.

suSUtoSU.name: suSUtoSU
suSUtoSU.description: It is peer-to-peer group this SU belongs to. With the SU to SU switch is turned on, SUs in the same peer-to-peer group can communicate to each other via the AP. There are totally 15 groups available. Note that the SU shall be set to priority user for this feature to improve latency.

suCIR.name: suCIR
suCIR.description: It is the Committed Information Rate (in Kbps) the AP allocates to SU.

suMIR.name: suMIR
suMIR.description: It is the Maximum Information Rate (in Kbps) the AP allocates to SU.

suRSSIFromSU.name: suRSSIFromSU
suRSSIFromSU.description: Subscriber unit RSSI from SU (in dBm).

suRSSIFromAP.name: suRSSIFromAP
suRSSIFromAP.description: Subscriber unit RSSI from AP (in dBm).

suTxPower.name: suTxPower
suTxPower.description: Subscriber unit Tx Power Level (in dBm).

suEthRxAvgThroughputLog.name: suEthRxAvgThroughputLog
suEthRxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) received on the Ethernet port over the period specified by suStatisticsSamplePeriod.

suEthTxAvgThroughputLog.name: suEthTxAvgThroughputLog
suEthTxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) transmitted on the Ethernet port over the period specified by suStatisticsSamplePeriod.

suRfRxAvgThroughputLog.name: suRfRxAvgThroughputLog
suRfRxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) received on the RF port over the period specified by suStatisticsSamplePeriod.

suRfTxAvgThroughputLog.name: suRfTxAvgThroughputLog
suRfTxAvgThroughputLog.description: Average payload data throughput (in Kbits/sec) transmitted on the RF port over the period specified by suStatisticsSamplePeriod.

suRfInOctets.name: suRfInOctets
suRfInOctets.description: Number of payload octets received on the RF port.

suRfOutOctets.name: suRfOutOctets
suRfOutOctets.description: Number of payload octets transmitted on the RF port.

suPowerLevel.name: suPowerLevel
suPowerLevel.description: It is a feature that is typically found in more elaborate mobile systems such as cellular CDMA networks. Using this feature, the SU has its RF power output adjusted until its signal strength received in the AP is roughly the same.

suTemperature.name: suTemperature
suTemperature.description: Subscriber Unit temperature reading value (in Celsius).

suReboot.name: suReboot
suReboot.description: AP issues reboot command to a specific subscriber unit.

suTCPIPForLocalEth.name: suTCPIPForLocalEth
suTCPIPForLocalEth.description: When it is turned on, then the SU will process all the local TCP/IP service.

trapconfigTrapTable.name: trapconfigTrapTable
trapconfigTrapTable.description: A table that contains information of Trango trap events .

trapconfigTrapEntry.name: trapconfigTrapEntry
trapconfigTrapEntry.description: Information about a specific Trango trap event.

aptrpEnable.name: aptrpEnable
aptrpEnable.description: Enable a specific Trango trap event or not.

suLinkUp.name: suLinkUp
suLinkUp.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a specific SU Associated.

suLinkDown.name: suLinkDown
suLinkDown.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a specific SU Powered Off.

apOpModeFailure.name: apOpModeFailure
apOpModeFailure.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a specific AP not being in ap mode during boot up sequence.
